Cell.Data: Verify that the clock is generated on the SCL line.
Verify that we are seeing the correct data on the SDA line.
Verifying that we have a valid value on SDA for every posedge of SCL.
When reset is active, SDA and SCL lines should be inactive
All coverpoints within the layered tb covergroup
"Ensure that all design units have 100% statement coverage 100% branch coverage"

Cell.ss:Data: Testing the enable bit of CSR register. Reason : After reset or power-up the Enable bit (E) has value '0'.

Cell.Data: Reading DPR register should return last byte received via I2C bus.
After a command is completed only one of the (DON,ACK,AL or ERR), checking this operation.
After a read command the status bits of CMDR need to retain their values and clear the interrupt output.
FSMR is a read only register.
Testing coverage of byte level fsm states
Testing coverage of bit level fsm state
Byte and Bit level FSM states combination
Testing cross coverage between byte level and bit level fsm states
After reset, the FSMs should be set to their idle states.
After the start command executes successfully, the bus should be taken and the FSM should reflect the same.
It is an error to send next command before previous command is completed. Such a command should be ignored.
When the IICMB core is disable the DUT should ignore all the commands sent to it.
The parameter written for the Set Bus command should be in range from 0 to g_num_bus – 1, otherwise the command returns ERROR status.
